03:03.267 --> 03:04.975
<i> ♪ Keep the colors</i>
<i> in the lines ♪</i>

03:04.977 --> 03:06.167
<i> ♪ Take flight ♪</i>

03:07.146 --> 03:10.147
[Faithful
by Me'Shell Ndegéocello plays]

03:33.380 --> 03:40.219
<i> ♪ My daddy made no excuse</i>
<i> I believe my lies are truth </i>

03:40.221 --> 03:44.014
<i> ♪ Why won't you eat</i>
<i> what you're fed ♪</i>

03:46.143 --> 03:51.813
<i> ♪ 'Cause when I touch myself</i>
<i> I think of only you ♪</i>

03:52.775 --> 03:56.151
<i> ♪ And when</i>
<i> I touch someone else ♪</i>

03:57.112 --> 04:00.906
<i> ♪ No one is faithful ♪</i>

04:01.867 --> 04:05.661
<i> ♪ I am weak, I'll go astray ♪</i>

04:09.833 --> 04:14.127
<i> ♪ Forgive me for my ways ♪</i>

04:16.757 --> 04:20.634
<i> ♪ No one is faithful ♪</i>

04:21.262 --> 04:22.302
Morning.

04:23.847 --> 04:25.305
Morning.

04:25.933 --> 04:27.808
-You're up early.
-Yeah.

04:29.520 --> 04:32.729
I... [clears throat]
I don't mean to rush you,

04:32.773 --> 04:36.525
but I'm heading out
to my Aunt Martha's.

04:38.279 --> 04:39.611
Martha's cousin, right?

04:41.907 --> 04:43.532
You remember that?

04:44.034 --> 04:45.450
[chuckles softly]

04:46.245 --> 04:47.327
I remember.

04:48.914 --> 04:51.790
She passed
a couple of months ago.

04:51.867 --> 04:56.295
She didn't leave a will,
but she signed her house over
to a local church, apparently,

04:56.297 --> 04:57.754
so I want
to pack up her things

04:57.756 --> 04:59.298
before they put
the house up for sale

04:59.300 --> 05:01.425
or whatever
they're gonna do with it.

05:01.844 --> 05:05.429
The... the church, I mean.

05:07.725 --> 05:11.101
I've been so disconnected
from the way I used to be.

05:13.355 --> 05:15.397
[voice shaking]
I used to be able
to hold someone's hands

05:15.399 --> 05:16.356
and...

05:18.235 --> 05:19.943
Understand things.

05:20.946 --> 05:24.406
I remember.
I don't think it's left you.

05:26.869 --> 05:28.243
It's way too deep.

05:30.914 --> 05:32.456
It's a deep part
of who you are.

05:35.794 --> 05:36.960
It's not gone, you'll find it.

05:47.348 --> 05:48.572
[sighs wearily]

05:52.227 --> 05:54.227
I'm gonna be heading out
in 20 minutes.

05:55.689 --> 05:56.605
Okay?

05:58.275 --> 05:59.191
Okay.

06:00.277 --> 06:01.151
[door opens]

06:02.196 --> 06:03.587
[door closes]

06:03.589 --> 06:04.821
[Faithful
by Me'Shell Ndegéocello
continues]

06:05.908 --> 06:09.743
<i> ♪ No one is faithful ♪</i>

06:11.121 --> 06:13.205
[Hollywood]
Somebody in Shreveport
registered it for auction.

06:13.207 --> 06:14.790
I don't know
who we're gonna ask for
when we get there,

06:14.866 --> 06:17.709
but we're gonna wing it.
[chuckles]

06:17.711 --> 06:21.129
Yeah, well,
I hope we don't find somebody
that want that land or lots.

06:21.715 --> 06:23.256
Damn Landrys.

06:23.258 --> 06:26.301
Hunting Ralph Angel
just like they did Ernest.

06:29.765 --> 06:31.890
Yeah, man.

06:31.967 --> 06:35.727
Hey, Prosper,
I know it's hard for you
to watch that land go, too.

06:38.148 --> 06:39.523
Wish there was...

06:40.692 --> 06:42.818
I was able to have done more.

06:44.988 --> 06:48.949
More I could still do.

06:56.333 --> 06:58.792
[bell dinging]

06:58.794 --> 07:03.964
This is the perfect,
most amazing,
incredible gift.

07:03.966 --> 07:05.382
-Thank you.
-Mmm-hmm.

07:05.384 --> 07:09.803
I have not had a manicure
in a very long time.

07:10.514 --> 07:12.264
-Least I could do.
-Mmm.

07:12.340 --> 07:14.474
Gramp's allowance
just sits in my drawer,

07:14.476 --> 07:15.892
-you know?
-Okay.

07:15.936 --> 07:17.686
Look after your sister
while I'm in there.

07:17.688 --> 07:18.828
-I will.
-See you later, babe.

07:18.830 --> 07:20.939
-Buh-bye. Have fun.
-[Tru gurgles]

07:20.941 --> 07:24.359
-Take care of Tru and Blue.
-Bye. I'll take care of her.
She good.

07:24.778 --> 07:26.027
-Hi.
-Hey.

07:29.158 --> 07:30.657
-I liked that.
-[chuckles]

07:32.161 --> 07:33.410
What's been going on
at school?

07:34.788 --> 07:35.996
Nothing.

07:36.874 --> 07:39.624
Man of many words.
Ain't got nothing to say?

07:39.626 --> 07:41.626
[chuckles] Come on, what's up?

07:43.380 --> 07:44.504
It's fine.

07:45.799 --> 07:49.050
I just don't... fit in.

07:50.637 --> 07:51.928
Somebody been mean to you?

07:55.184 --> 07:56.141
Blue.

07:56.727 --> 07:58.977
Somebody bullying you?

07:58.979 --> 08:01.938
No, it's not
a bullying situation
or anything.

08:01.940 --> 08:08.195
It's... [sighs] it's just that
I don't really vibe with them,

08:08.271 --> 08:10.530
and they don't really get me.

08:11.867 --> 08:13.533
Guess we grew up differently.

08:22.920 --> 08:25.587
Look, I know you might want
to fit in sometimes,

08:25.664 --> 08:28.632
but there ain't nothing wrong
with being different.

08:29.426 --> 08:30.967
Just 'cause
you raised different

08:31.011 --> 08:32.928
don't mean you don't belong
like all them other kids,

08:33.347 --> 08:34.262
and don't forget it.

08:47.319 --> 08:48.527
Blue.

08:52.241 --> 08:53.949
You know your mama
went to the same school?

08:57.955 --> 08:59.621
Biological father did, too.

09:01.416 --> 09:02.999
-What?
-Yeah.

09:03.794 --> 09:05.043
I think you should know.

09:06.296 --> 09:09.256
I've been finding out
a lot about him.

09:09.258 --> 09:10.715
I don't want
to hide something from you.

09:11.301 --> 09:12.458
Okay.

09:14.513 --> 09:16.137
Him and Mommy
went to school together.

09:19.810 --> 09:21.393
Then we fell in love.

09:22.104 --> 09:23.728
She said I could be
Blue's daddy.

09:26.358 --> 09:28.817
What about him?
What did he say?

09:32.948 --> 09:33.863
He said, "Okay."

09:35.200 --> 09:36.658
[sighs wearily]

09:37.536 --> 09:38.702
'Cause he didn't want to be.

09:44.126 --> 09:45.500
That make you feel
some type of way?

09:46.295 --> 09:47.586
[sighs]

09:48.213 --> 09:53.258
I didn't really know him
so it doesn't matter,

09:53.335 --> 09:59.222
and he didn't really know me,
so it's not like it's personal
or anything.

10:01.143 --> 10:02.726
Guess he just didn't want
to be a father.

10:05.355 --> 10:06.229
I did.

10:07.566 --> 10:09.107
A lot.

10:09.109 --> 10:11.026
If you ask me,
I think I got pretty lucky.

10:12.154 --> 10:13.903
-I think I got lucky, too.
-Oh, yeah?

10:14.489 --> 10:15.530
Come here.

10:22.581 --> 10:24.372
Look.

10:24.374 --> 10:29.210
Point is,
you belong at that school
and anywhere you want to be.

10:30.047 --> 10:31.212
Don't ever forget it.

10:32.090 --> 10:34.883
Remember your roots, okay?

10:34.885 --> 10:36.593
I think I'm a pretty
interesting person.

10:36.595 --> 10:38.595
-I think so, too.
-[chuckles]

10:38.639 --> 10:40.513
-From an interesting place.
-[chuckles]

10:40.849 --> 10:43.058
[Tru giggles]

10:43.093 --> 10:44.768
-[chuckles]
-What's so funny, huh?

10:44.770 --> 10:46.728
-You know it, Tru.
-[Tru laughs]

10:48.357 --> 10:50.899
What you laughin' at, huh?
[chuckles softly]

10:54.571 --> 10:59.115
[sighs] Blue,
mind doing me a favor?

11:00.952 --> 11:02.535
Don't tell Mommy
about this, too,

11:02.537 --> 11:04.788
-until I can
talk to her, okay?
-Sure, Pops.,

11:04.790 --> 11:05.955
You got me?

11:07.000 --> 11:08.958
[exhales and chuckles]

11:11.546 --> 11:12.796
[bell jingles]

11:13.965 --> 11:16.257
-Hey.
-Hey, Billie.

11:20.055 --> 11:21.805
Hey. When's your flight?

11:21.807 --> 11:24.724
I thought you would be
in LA with your mama
by now.

11:24.726 --> 11:28.019
[sighs]
We got into a disagreement.
I'm not going.

11:30.065 --> 11:32.065
A disagreement?

11:32.067 --> 11:34.359
She's two days away
from the biggest day
of her life.

11:34.361 --> 11:37.028
What could you possibly
disagree with her about

11:37.030 --> 11:40.281
-that would cause you
to not be there for her?
-She said some things,

11:40.283 --> 11:42.617
and I don't feel comfortable
being there with her.

11:43.787 --> 11:45.704
And honestly,
I don't think
she wants me there.

11:46.832 --> 11:48.915
-What on Earth?
-[doorbell jingling]

11:49.543 --> 11:52.711
-Hey, Vi, save my...
-Yeah, baby, please.

11:52.713 --> 11:54.421
-Micah.
-[Billie] Hi,
welcome to Vi's Prized Pies.

11:54.423 --> 11:58.133
You need to get on a plane
and get out there.

11:58.135 --> 12:00.343
You're the only one
who can go.

12:01.471 --> 12:03.304
You're the only one
that can be there
to support her

12:03.306 --> 12:05.265
on her election night.

12:05.267 --> 12:08.601
You know the rest of us
got to be here
the next morning

12:08.603 --> 12:10.478
-for the auction.
-[sighs]

12:10.480 --> 12:13.189
And our foster assignment
could happen any day.

12:13.191 --> 12:14.816
No one else can go.

12:15.610 --> 12:18.611
-You want her to be alone?
-My dad is there.

12:18.613 --> 12:20.530
Her California friends,
her staff.

12:20.532 --> 12:21.614
She's fine.

12:22.159 --> 12:23.825
What are you thinking, Micah?

12:25.454 --> 12:29.539
You need to get there
and stand with your mother.

12:29.541 --> 12:31.958
-I'm asking you to do this.
-Don't ask me to do that.

12:33.003 --> 12:34.919
This is the same issue
I have with her.

12:34.996 --> 12:37.589
All these demands being made
about what I wanna do.

12:37.591 --> 12:39.799
I'm a grown man. Respect that.

12:43.138 --> 12:44.637
You lower your mouth.

12:48.435 --> 12:52.312
So you think this is how
grown men act?

12:54.649 --> 12:56.691
Not showing up
for your people?

13:03.950 --> 13:05.158
[doorbell jingling]

13:08.705 --> 13:10.330
Somebody here
registered a bid.

13:11.249 --> 13:13.458
Hey, good afternoon.
How you doing today, ma'am?

13:13.460 --> 13:16.294
-I'm good. How are you?
-Well, I'm blessed
and highly favored,

13:16.296 --> 13:20.256
but my goodness,
y'all have one mighty fine
operation here.

13:20.258 --> 13:23.468
Quick question.
Where do you source
your cane juice from

13:23.545 --> 13:25.887
-to make your rum?
-We have six varieties,

13:25.889 --> 13:27.931
and we have cane
from three different parishes.

13:27.933 --> 13:29.849
Three different parishes, huh?

13:29.851 --> 13:32.060
Does Saint Josephine
happen to be
one of those parishes?

13:32.687 --> 13:34.938
I don't know.
The boss would know.

13:34.940 --> 13:37.232
-Is he here right now?
-[man] Sure is.

13:40.111 --> 13:41.027
Hello, gentlemen.

13:45.617 --> 13:47.325
[car radio plays]

13:47.327 --> 13:49.452
-[Ralph] You want
an ice cream sandwich?
-[Blue] Already know.

13:49.454 --> 13:51.871
-[Blue] You want one, Mom?
-[Ralph] What about you, Mama?

13:51.948 --> 13:54.916
[chuckles] I'm okay.
We have ice cream at home.

13:54.993 --> 13:56.292
Sometimes
I like homemade better.

13:57.671 --> 13:58.670
Okay.

13:59.130 --> 14:01.047
Home is better sometimes.

14:04.427 --> 14:06.678
-[car engine
and radio turns off]
-I'll be back.

14:11.935 --> 14:13.518
How's everything going
at Grandma's?

14:14.563 --> 14:15.520
How's school?

14:16.398 --> 14:19.566
-Fine.
-Just fine?

14:19.568 --> 14:23.069
-That's it.
-Well, I talked
to Pops about it

14:23.071 --> 14:25.446
and he's right.

14:25.448 --> 14:27.615
I just have to remember
that I deserve to be there

14:27.617 --> 14:29.325
as much as
any other kid there.

14:29.870 --> 14:31.828
I have an alumni legacy, too.

14:31.830 --> 14:35.331
Double as much
as most kids there do,

14:35.375 --> 14:39.502
and I have to remember that
whenever I feel like
I miss home or anything.

14:40.964 --> 14:41.921
Yeah.

14:42.257 --> 14:43.214
Absolutely.

14:44.843 --> 14:46.050
What do you mean by double?

14:49.431 --> 14:50.722
I mean you, Mom.

14:51.725 --> 14:52.724
You're an alumnus.

14:53.268 --> 14:54.684
You said double.

14:56.271 --> 14:59.063
Yeah, Grandma.

15:03.028 --> 15:04.694
You know
Grandma didn't go there.

15:06.865 --> 15:10.700
You're right.
I get confused sometimes.

15:13.371 --> 15:15.071
[sighs softly]

15:22.172 --> 15:28.301
Here we take fresh cane juice
and make cane spirit rum...

15:30.639 --> 15:32.338
Like you ain't never tasted.

15:43.276 --> 15:48.196
-Mmm. Clean.
-Slightly grassy notes.
It's pretty damn good.

15:48.198 --> 15:53.618
Why battle my uncle
with all his issues
when I could be here,

15:54.454 --> 15:58.665
five hours away, on my own,
doing this?

15:58.667 --> 16:02.001
So, if you're not registered
for the auction,

16:02.629 --> 16:04.087
somebody's using your name.

16:04.089 --> 16:07.131
Maybe
it's an auto registration.

16:07.133 --> 16:11.177
You know, you pay
to be automatically registered
in all state auctions.

16:11.179 --> 16:13.096
I probably forgot
to turn it off.

16:13.139 --> 16:15.014
I will look into it.

16:16.935 --> 16:18.226
[sighs]

16:21.147 --> 16:23.898
I'm done with all that,
with all of 'em.

16:23.975 --> 16:25.233
Your family?

16:25.235 --> 16:26.234
Yeah.

16:27.654 --> 16:29.946
You can't decide who they are.

16:31.908 --> 16:33.700
But you can decide
who you are.

16:35.453 --> 16:36.953
I'm making
a difference choice.

16:40.291 --> 16:42.250
I have to stay far away
from my family,

16:43.461 --> 16:45.211
or they'll pull me back in.

16:48.299 --> 16:49.716
I just can't let that happen.

16:52.929 --> 16:54.262
I wish you all the best.

16:55.640 --> 16:56.681
[Hollywood] Yes indeed.

16:57.350 --> 16:58.516
Good luck with all that.

17:10.613 --> 17:12.321
♪ <i> It feels good♪</i>

17:13.074 --> 17:14.032
♪ <i> Yeah♪</i>

17:14.868 --> 17:16.617
♪ <i> It feels good♪</i>

17:19.122 --> 17:20.246
♪ <i> It feels good♪</i>

17:22.500 --> 17:24.042
Who's ready for cobbler?

17:26.588 --> 17:28.212
♪ <i> So good good to me♪</i>

17:32.010 --> 17:34.761
Yeah, I bet you these folks
go for pies.

17:34.763 --> 17:39.599
Company's done some kind
of promotion on the 'Gram
or the TikTok or one of them

17:39.675 --> 17:43.227
and folks have found out
that there's a real Vi's Pies.

17:43.646 --> 17:45.229
Look at this madness.

17:45.306 --> 17:46.898
[Nova chuckles softly]
It's wonderful.

17:46.900 --> 17:49.692
Stressful, but wonderful.
Aunt Vi, you're famous.

17:49.694 --> 17:50.735
Well, I don't want it.

17:50.737 --> 17:52.144
And if you hadn't come

17:52.221 --> 17:54.030
-I don't know
what I would've done.
-I'm here.

17:54.699 --> 17:55.239
We got this.

17:55.241 --> 17:56.982
[bell dinging]

17:56.984 --> 17:59.160
-Two meatless sandwiches
and three gumbo lunches.
-All right.

17:59.162 --> 18:00.745
Six blackberry
cobbler slices...

18:00.747 --> 18:02.872
-Okay.
-...four chocolate heaven
whole pies,

18:02.907 --> 18:05.666
-and a chicken pecan salad
with hot honey mustard.
-[Vi] Wait, wait.

18:05.668 --> 18:07.543
This is the last
of to-go lunches,

18:07.587 --> 18:10.630
you tell the to-go's
that it's only pies to go.

18:10.706 --> 18:12.465
Full menu
for seated guests only.

18:12.467 --> 18:15.176
And, Billie,
don't you dillydally,
you drop those checks

18:15.253 --> 18:18.513
as soon as you see them
on their second to last bite,
all right?

18:18.589 --> 18:20.681
-[Billie] I--
-[Vi] Tell them we are out
of pecan chicken,

18:20.758 --> 18:22.767
-offer fried.
-Okay.

18:22.844 --> 18:25.853
I can't do this,
it's too much.

18:25.930 --> 18:28.815
I mean, I'm expecting
a foster child any day now.

18:29.943 --> 18:31.317
Why would this happen now?

18:32.362 --> 18:34.153
Count your blessings, Aunt Vi.

18:34.155 --> 18:37.532
What if I can't handle
the child right now?

18:38.785 --> 18:41.452
Maybe there was a reason
why it never happened.

18:44.249 --> 18:45.623
Maybe it wasn't meant to be.

18:47.460 --> 18:49.127
-[deep breath]
-Breathe,

18:49.712 --> 18:50.628
Aunt Vi.

18:53.758 --> 18:55.341
[breathing together]

18:58.763 --> 19:01.722
-All is well.
-[deep exhale]

19:02.350 --> 19:03.307
Say it with me.

19:06.020 --> 19:07.145
[deep exhale]

19:08.148 --> 19:09.397
[both] All is well.

19:12.861 --> 19:14.026
You got this.

19:14.737 --> 19:16.612
-All is well.
-All is well.

19:19.200 --> 19:20.199
All right.

