at that age.

35:13.403 --> 35:15.003
-They want babies.
-Right.

35:15.005 --> 35:17.864
So, she's been
to three foster homes
in 12 months.

35:17.866 --> 35:21.409
She's tried
to keep up her grades,
but it's been hard.

35:21.411 --> 35:23.620
-I think that--
-She's prefect for us.

35:25.874 --> 35:28.458
She's perfect for us.
[chuckles]

35:29.837 --> 35:33.296
She's perfect, she's perfect.

35:33.298 --> 35:36.174
-[Nova] Wow, this is amazing.
-She's perfect for us.

35:36.176 --> 35:38.218
We've got a new Bordelon.

35:38.220 --> 35:39.427
I thank you.

35:40.389 --> 35:42.722
-Thank you.
-She's perfect for us.

35:43.433 --> 35:45.058
I can bring her
to you tomorrow.

35:56.113 --> 35:57.612
My parents are asleep.

36:00.033 --> 36:01.324
The auction is in the morning.

36:03.453 --> 36:05.162
What are you doing here?

36:06.790 --> 36:10.208
-You shouldn't've come.
-I ain't drive here to fight.
Okay.

36:11.670 --> 36:14.796
Look, you say I should
use my words, you push me
to use my words,

36:14.798 --> 36:16.673
I've been trying
to talk to you for weeks

36:17.301 --> 36:19.176
about this Blue
and Chase thing.

36:19.178 --> 36:20.594
-There is no Blue and Chase--
-There is.

36:20.762 --> 36:22.596
Stop saying that.

36:22.672 --> 36:24.556
You're the one
that keeps connecting
them making it a thing,

36:24.558 --> 36:25.515
you could not let it go.

36:25.517 --> 36:27.309
No I can't let it go.

36:27.394 --> 36:29.144
I'm sorry.

36:29.146 --> 36:31.688
Maybe I shouldn't've
told him like that, but I did.

36:31.690 --> 36:34.316
Oh, you're so righteous
when it comes to Blue, right?

36:34.318 --> 36:37.194
You know, you don't wanna
tell him things, you wanna
be honest about everything.

36:38.113 --> 36:39.178
And what's wrong with that?

36:39.990 --> 36:41.740
How does your commitment
to honesty

36:41.742 --> 36:45.160
factor in to you instructing
our son to lie to his mother?

36:45.162 --> 36:46.995
-That's not what I said.
-[scoffs] What'd ya say?

36:47.915 --> 36:49.447
I told him to let me
talk to you first

36:49.524 --> 36:51.708
-because I wanted you
to hear it from me.
-Mmm-hmm.

36:52.794 --> 36:54.711
There's a difference.
Look, I'm sorry.

36:55.297 --> 36:56.504
-For tell--
-You're sorry?

36:58.133 --> 36:59.216
I don't believe you.

37:04.389 --> 37:06.181
I don't trust you.

37:09.728 --> 37:11.144
You don't trust me, Darla?

37:11.146 --> 37:13.396
After you ran up out the city
with my daughter.

37:13.857 --> 37:15.232
Without telling me.

37:15.234 --> 37:17.359
You got the nerve to tell me
that you don't trust me.

37:18.862 --> 37:21.029
You remember
what I said to you
at that parking lot?

37:24.243 --> 37:26.618
-Remember what I told you?
-Don't you do that.

37:26.620 --> 37:28.995
I said, "All I have to do
is think about your life

37:29.706 --> 37:31.414
whenever I thought
my life was bad."

37:32.960 --> 37:34.793
It's probably the worst thing
I could've said at the time.

37:35.504 --> 37:37.170
'Cause my life was bad.

37:38.465 --> 37:40.632
But you know
what I think about
when I look at you today?

37:42.511 --> 37:44.243
You know what I see?

37:45.681 --> 37:48.431
I see somebody
who probably loves me
more than I love myself.

37:50.102 --> 37:51.226
On most days.

37:53.272 --> 37:54.604
And I'm sorry for it.

37:55.691 --> 37:58.066
Maybe it didn't come out
the right way, but...

37:58.110 --> 38:00.944
[inhales] that's why
I've been trying to talk.

38:00.946 --> 38:03.071
I can't do no more secrets.

38:03.073 --> 38:04.864
That's what messed up
the family, that's what...

38:05.534 --> 38:06.950
That's what we've been
running from.

38:07.911 --> 38:09.411
That's what's been
messing us up.

38:10.539 --> 38:12.414
So, what do we do now, Darla?

38:13.166 --> 38:14.499
[sighs]

38:32.936 --> 38:34.728
-Wow!
-What do you think, brother?

38:35.772 --> 38:36.896
-It's magical, bro.
-Morning.

38:36.898 --> 38:38.315
[both] Hey.

38:38.317 --> 38:40.191
Aunt Vi asked me
to pick up an envelope
from you.

38:40.193 --> 38:41.609
Oh, yeah.
It's on the top left drawer.

38:41.611 --> 38:43.153
Hey, you! Come here.

38:43.155 --> 38:44.738
-I'll be back in two shakes,
all right?
-All right, bet.

38:44.814 --> 38:47.324
For the auction!
Know what, let me show you.

38:48.035 --> 38:49.326
Excuse me, doll.

38:49.328 --> 38:50.702
So, this is what I want...

38:51.955 --> 38:52.996
[Remy] Okay...

38:54.541 --> 38:57.542
-Tell me everything.
-[laughs] You!

38:57.619 --> 38:59.085
You got the most,
you go first.

38:59.162 --> 39:02.255
No, I don't think
I've got the most.

39:02.257 --> 39:04.841
You're the one
with all the books and movies.

39:04.843 --> 39:09.512
Hell, you got the wife,
kids, big job.

39:09.589 --> 39:11.056
-Okay. We're both
doing all right.
-Yeah.

39:11.132 --> 39:12.182
-We're both doing
all right.
-We are.

39:12.184 --> 39:13.808
[both chuckle]

39:13.810 --> 39:17.562
[sighs] It's wild seeing you
after all this time.

39:17.564 --> 39:19.189
You're the same,
but different.

39:19.775 --> 39:20.881
Grown.

39:20.883 --> 39:23.109
-Why, thank you.
-[both chuckle]

39:24.988 --> 39:27.697
No, you know,
I feel grown...

39:28.492 --> 39:30.784
'cause I feel settled,
finally.

39:30.860 --> 39:32.427
You know what I mean?

39:32.429 --> 39:37.248
We all have to find
what settled means to us
and...

39:37.250 --> 39:39.292
you know, I guess I found it.

39:41.296 --> 39:42.504
Have you?

39:45.675 --> 39:48.468
Wow. That's a good question.

39:50.597 --> 39:52.514
I guess,
if I had to think about it...

39:53.683 --> 39:57.894
I'm not,
but I'm closer than I was.

39:57.971 --> 39:59.211
-Okay.
-[Hollywood shouting] Remy!

39:59.289 --> 40:01.189
-Yo?
-[Hollywood] Bust a move,
brother!

40:01.191 --> 40:04.359
-Yup, yup!
I'll see you there?
-[Nova] Definitely.

40:05.862 --> 40:08.571
And thank you.

40:08.573 --> 40:11.741
This plan, if it works,
we'll get our land back.

40:11.818 --> 40:15.328
It's huge. It's everything
we want and need.

40:18.166 --> 40:19.732
It's gonna work.

40:30.387 --> 40:32.220
I'm gonna get
another cup of coffee
before we leave.

40:32.264 --> 40:33.721
-All right.
-[Billie chuckles]

40:36.351 --> 40:39.060
[sighs] It's good
to see Remy, wasn't it?

40:39.062 --> 40:42.730
It is. It's strange, though.

40:42.765 --> 40:45.942
So many people from my past
have come back into
my life recently.

40:46.019 --> 40:48.002
I kind of don't know
what to make of it.

40:48.004 --> 40:51.281
I feel like it's all
trying to tell me something,
but I don't know what.

40:51.283 --> 40:52.282
[hesitates] I...

40:53.368 --> 40:55.410
I'm babbling. [laughs]

40:55.454 --> 40:57.787
-I'm sorry.
-[Billie] Oh, girl.
No, don't worry about that.

40:57.789 --> 40:59.664
You sorting through
your past like that?

41:00.792 --> 41:04.878
I mean,
it changed my life,
changed everything.

41:04.880 --> 41:07.422
Seeing you girls right now
reminds me of the time

41:07.424 --> 41:09.215
Ernest and I were
talking about you.

41:11.928 --> 41:13.219
Yeah, it was...

41:15.390 --> 41:16.764
It was a hard day.

41:18.143 --> 41:21.728
<i> Billie, it was</i>
<i> your mama's funeral.</i>

41:25.859 --> 41:27.609
[sighs]

41:32.741 --> 41:34.908
-[Ernest] You all right?
-Yeah, I'm good.

41:34.910 --> 41:36.117
Thank you for coming.

41:40.790 --> 41:42.390
[sighs] Mmm.

41:43.460 --> 41:47.670
-You didn't have
to make that drive.
-You kidding?

41:47.672 --> 41:50.548
I wouldn't have missed it.
How you holding up?

41:50.550 --> 41:52.675
Oh, you know,
best I can.

41:53.512 --> 41:55.220
Trying to deal
with Billie.

41:56.139 --> 41:57.722
She wasn't going to come...

41:57.724 --> 42:00.058
to her mother's funeral
if it was in Louisiana.

42:00.060 --> 42:02.101
Swore she was never
coming back to St Jo.

42:03.021 --> 42:04.896
[scoffs]

42:04.898 --> 42:07.649
-That girl's a handful,
ain't it?
-[chuckles]

42:07.651 --> 42:10.693
You got that right.
Mmm, mmm, mmm.

42:11.238 --> 42:12.946
[chuckling] Sit down.

42:18.578 --> 42:21.704
Prosper,
count it as a blessing.

42:21.706 --> 42:25.959
Claire was in Billie's life
as an adult.

42:28.463 --> 42:30.797
I think that's one
of the things with Nova.

42:31.675 --> 42:34.175
Trudy wasn't there
to help guide her...

42:34.844 --> 42:36.219
tell her things...

42:37.931 --> 42:39.931
that I can't tell her
or couldn't tell her.

42:39.933 --> 42:41.307
I didn't know how.

42:45.772 --> 42:46.896
When...

42:47.732 --> 42:48.982
me and Trudy...

42:49.818 --> 42:52.652
finally broke up,
that last time,

42:52.654 --> 42:54.404
she said to me,
she said...

42:58.660 --> 42:59.993
She said, "Ernest...

43:01.371 --> 43:04.163
love goes its own way,
just like the river.

43:04.165 --> 43:07.375
You can't force it
or make it go your way.

43:09.212 --> 43:10.420
If you smart...

43:11.631 --> 43:13.381
you'll just...

43:14.301 --> 43:15.300
flow with it."

43:18.138 --> 43:20.054
Wise woman. Wise woman.

43:22.684 --> 43:23.975
Our daughters...

43:25.020 --> 43:27.395
will be wise one day too...

43:28.732 --> 43:30.732
when they come
to understand that...

43:32.193 --> 43:34.110
it doesn't matter
how love comes...

43:35.697 --> 43:39.032
rich, poor, man, woman...

43:40.952 --> 43:43.328
black, white...

43:46.082 --> 43:49.626
here or hereafter...

43:51.963 --> 43:54.964
it flows its own way...

43:56.468 --> 44:00.011
and you gotta flow with it.

44:15.320 --> 44:18.696
Co-op funds, Charley's meal
collateral, and Hollywood
and Vi's contribution

44:18.698 --> 44:20.180
we had 250 K.

44:20.182 --> 44:23.117
And then that big,
anonymous donation
out of D.C.

44:23.119 --> 44:24.994
brought us to 450,000.

44:24.996 --> 44:27.830
And Betty's farm
as collateral gave...
another...

44:27.832 --> 44:28.956
75 k.

44:28.958 --> 44:30.708
So then we put in
the movie money

44:30.743 --> 44:32.627
we've got 750 K to bid with.

44:34.422 --> 44:36.047
So if none of the farmer's
bid against us,

44:36.049 --> 44:37.674
we might actually have a shot.

44:38.760 --> 44:39.759
Look who's over there.

44:40.804 --> 44:42.345
<i> ♪ Beautiful one ♪</i>

44:42.347 --> 44:43.763
<i> ♪ It's so beautiful ♪</i>

44:43.765 --> 44:44.847
Remy.

44:44.849 --> 44:46.015
A back up.

44:46.092 --> 44:48.184
Ra, no matter who else
pops up...

44:48.728 --> 44:50.144
...stick to the plan.

44:50.146 --> 44:52.563
<i> ♪ Oh, beautiful people ♪</i>

44:52.565 --> 44:53.748
<i> ♪ Boys and girls ♪</i>

44:53.750 --> 44:55.024
Now we've been under
Landrys enough.

44:56.027 --> 44:57.276
Today we take it back.

44:58.029 --> 44:59.395
All right.

44:59.397 --> 45:01.197
<i> ♪ Get up and dance</i>
<i> Beautiful world ♪</i>

45:01.199 --> 45:02.699
[gavel banging]

45:02.775 --> 45:03.950
All right!

45:05.120 --> 45:07.870
Before we get
to the foreclosed land,

45:07.872 --> 45:10.164
we got some good
equipment here
on the docket.

45:10.166 --> 45:14.627
First up, lot 124,
John Deere 7830,
low miles.

45:18.216 --> 45:19.257
[gavel bangs] Sold!

45:20.844 --> 45:22.777
Next up.

45:22.779 --> 45:26.305
Three excellent tracks
of land in St. Josephine
sellin' as one unit.

45:26.307 --> 45:31.352
The bulk of this land has been
in the Landry-Boudreaux family
for over a century.

45:31.396 --> 45:33.730
With two new parcels added
this past year.

45:33.732 --> 45:35.064
You got this, Ra.

45:35.141 --> 45:37.275
[auctioneer] 800 acre lot
and foreclosure,

45:37.277 --> 45:39.902
200 acres as historical
landmark,

45:39.904 --> 45:42.739
600 acres for farm use.

45:42.815 --> 45:45.199
Starting bid at $250,000.

45:45.994 --> 45:47.034
Auction on, here!

45:47.078 --> 45:48.244
250.

45:48.246 --> 45:49.695
-Do I have 250?
-[man] Hey, Ra.

45:50.498 --> 45:52.999
You got our support always,
we got your back, man.

45:53.075 --> 45:54.917
-Yeah.
-[man 2] We got your
back, man.

45:57.213 --> 45:59.630
[auctioneer] Asking 250,
do I hear 250?

45:59.707 --> 46:01.299
250! Do I hear 250?

46:01.375 --> 46:02.884
Shake that cat.

46:03.386 --> 46:05.486
250!

46:05.488 --> 46:08.556
First bid from the man
in the front left, 250,000,
thank you very much, sir.

46:08.600 --> 46:10.183
$250,000 down here,
now who'll give me 300?

46:10.259 --> 46:11.993
Can I see 300, anybody 300?

46:11.995 --> 46:14.562
Asking 300,
300 from the gentleman
over here on the right.

46:14.606 --> 46:16.731
$300,000 down here,
now who can give me 400?

46:16.775 --> 46:18.399
Whatever y'all
pooled together,

46:18.443 --> 46:20.526
my folks are prepared
to double it.

46:20.528 --> 46:24.572
Why don't you just save us
all some time, tell us how
much you got...

46:24.616 --> 46:25.948
...and we'll call it a day.

46:25.950 --> 46:27.200
[auctioneer] 400,
asking 400. Anybody?

46:27.202 --> 46:28.618
[Ralph] 400!

46:28.620 --> 46:30.119
-[crowd gasps]
-[auctioneer] Thank you
very much.

46:30.121 --> 46:31.287
For the Bordelon's,
400 down here.

46:31.289 --> 46:32.413
Now do I see 450?

46:32.415 --> 46:33.956
[woman] 450?

46:33.958 --> 46:35.666
-450!
-450 right here.

46:35.668 --> 46:36.959
-[crowd gasps]
-Gentleman on the right, 450.

46:36.961 --> 46:38.002
Now asking 500.

46:38.004 --> 46:39.203
500 right here!

46:39.205 --> 46:40.755
$500,000 down here,
now what about 550?

46:40.757 --> 46:42.173
-750.
-[crowd gasping]

46:44.344 --> 46:46.260
750 from this gentleman
right here.

46:46.262 --> 46:47.595
-750, now who'll give me 800?
-That's it.

46:48.139 --> 46:49.288
That's all we got.

46:49.290 --> 46:50.431
[auctioneer] 800 anybody?
800 anybody?

46:52.101 --> 46:53.518
750 here right here, 750.

46:53.594 --> 46:54.477
Can I see 800?

46:54.554 --> 46:55.520
Going once...

46:55.939 --> 46:57.647
-Going twice...
-800.

46:57.649 --> 46:59.398
-[crowd clammers]
-[auctioneer]
800 right there in the middle.

46:59.400 --> 47:00.608
Come on 850.

47:00.652 --> 47:01.818
850 anybody?

47:02.862 --> 47:04.362
That'll give me 850. 850.

47:04.364 --> 47:05.947
850.

47:05.949 --> 47:08.533
850 right here,
now who give me, uh,
875?

47:08.535 --> 47:09.733
875.

47:09.735 --> 47:11.244
[auctioneer] 875 right here,
come on now.

47:11.246 --> 47:12.870
900, how 'bout 900?

47:12.872 --> 47:14.221
900.

47:14.223 --> 47:15.665
-[crowd clammers]
-[auctioneer] How 'bout 925?

47:15.667 --> 47:16.707
About 925?

47:16.709 --> 47:17.667
925.

47:17.669 --> 47:20.002
925 right here, how about 950.

47:20.004 --> 47:20.670
-950.
-[crowd clammers]

47:20.672 --> 47:22.396
950!

47:22.398 --> 47:24.757
-How much is Remy
allowed of ours to spend?
-[Nova] Not sure.

47:25.385 --> 47:26.509
How 'bout 975?

47:35.103 --> 47:36.102
One million.

47:36.104 --> 47:37.895
[crowd gasping]

47:37.897 --> 47:39.522
On behalf of Texas Valley A&M.

47:49.075 --> 47:50.116
Going once...

47:53.705 --> 47:54.954
Going twice...

47:54.956 --> 47:56.080
[Jacob] 1.1 million.

47:56.082 --> 47:57.689
[crowd gasps]

48:04.215 --> 48:07.008
[auctioneer] 1.1 million
from the gentleman
in the back.

48:07.510 --> 48:08.426
Going once...

48:08.761 --> 48:10.636
Going twice...

48:10.638 --> 48:12.346
Gotta keep it in the family.

48:12.348 --> 48:15.308
[auctioneer] Sold!
The Landry lot is sold.

48:28.364 --> 48:29.822
Might need a movin' van.

48:31.409 --> 48:32.825
I'll leave the large furniture
to the church

48:32.827 --> 48:34.160
she gave the house to.

48:35.371 --> 48:38.372
But these photos
and family heirlooms,

48:38.374 --> 48:39.498
I can't just leave them here.

48:43.838 --> 48:44.828
Thanks for helping.

48:46.966 --> 48:48.466
I'll always come
when you call.

48:50.219 --> 48:52.094
<i> ♪ Ah ♪</i>

48:52.096 --> 48:54.430
[Violet] Everybody
loves bikes.

48:54.507 --> 48:55.806
[Hollywood] I know I do.

48:55.808 --> 48:57.266
-Hey!
-[Hollywood laughs] Come on.

48:57.343 --> 48:59.644
<i> ♪ Slip Away ♪</i>

48:59.646 --> 49:00.978
[Violet] Oh,
that feels better.

49:01.055 --> 49:02.980
It's close by.

49:03.057 --> 49:05.399
<i> ♪ Through my fingers ♪</i>

49:06.027 --> 49:09.195
<i> ♪ When you left ♪</i>

49:09.864 --> 49:13.824
<i> ♪ Oh, you took away ♪</i>

49:13.826 --> 49:17.495
<i> ♪ Some part of me ♪</i>

49:17.830 --> 49:19.372
I'm so sorry, Mom.

49:19.448 --> 49:20.373
<i> ♪ I think I needed ♪</i>

49:20.375 --> 49:21.374
Come here.

49:22.168 --> 49:23.292
I should've come earlier.

49:24.337 --> 49:25.753
I should've been here.

49:25.755 --> 49:27.505
<i> ♪ You'll always be</i>
<i> A part of me ♪</i>

49:27.507 --> 49:28.589
Mmm.

49:29.926 --> 49:32.677
<i> ♪ And wherever I go ♪</i>

49:32.679 --> 49:38.099
<i> ♪ I'll always know</i>
<i> That you're near ♪</i>

49:38.101 --> 49:40.643
<i> ♪ Oh, the tears from my eyes ♪</i>

49:40.645 --> 49:41.644
Welcome home, Polly.

49:43.064 --> 49:45.648
We are so happy
that you're here.

49:45.650 --> 49:49.443
<i> ♪ You're the best</i>
<i> Of my thoughts ♪</i>

49:49.487 --> 49:52.571
It's a firm offer from Leap.

49:53.408 --> 49:54.782
Based in LA
but they're opening

49:54.784 --> 49:56.367
a new office in New York City.

49:57.120 --> 50:00.746
I would be the program
coordinator...

50:00.823 --> 50:02.707
...reporting directly
to the Senior VP.

50:03.543 --> 50:06.961
Salary, benefits, everything.

50:06.963 --> 50:10.631
And their motto
is, "Change
is ours to create".

50:10.633 --> 50:12.174
Isn't that great?

50:12.251 --> 50:14.635
It's everything I've
ever wanted.

50:14.679 --> 50:16.887
I could even amplify
artists from the collective.

50:16.889 --> 50:18.472
[Charley] You're perfect
for it.

50:19.600 --> 50:21.017
Your experience.

50:21.936 --> 50:23.644
Your passion.

50:23.688 --> 50:26.272
And your high profile
to benefit to them.

50:26.274 --> 50:28.274
It means a lot
that you see that now.

50:28.350 --> 50:32.695
<i> ♪ I pray just to see</i>
<i> Your face ♪</i>

50:32.772 --> 50:33.988
[knocking]

50:33.990 --> 50:36.949
♪ <i> In my dreams♪</i>

50:37.910 --> 50:39.994
♪ <i> In my dreams♪</i>

50:39.996 --> 50:40.828
Can I help ya?

